Author: Sean <sean@openclaw.ai>
Date:   Sat Jun 20 15:53:32 2026 +0800

    feat: add cooperative cancellation to DAGScheduler
    
    Add threading.Event cancel_event flag to DAGScheduler. Set the event when
    any stage exceeds its deadline so executor callables can check
    cancel_event.is_set() before file-system mutations. This prevents orphan
    threads from continuing to modify files after the scheduler has abandoned
    the stage.
    
    - DAGScheduler.cancel_event: threading.Event, set on timeout, cleared at
      start of each execute_parallel call
    - Orchestrator exec_stage: checks cancel_event before agent invocation
    - ARCHITECTURE.md: documents DAG mode as experimental with known limitations
    - Tests: 4 new tests covering normal execution, timeout, clear-between-calls,
      and executor observation of cancel_event
    
    pytest tests/test_pipeline.py -q: 72 passed
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>

